cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

The paper deals with the problem of semantic image segmentation using deep learning techniques, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) domain. The proposed method involves ensembling of different classifiers, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of Copula functions for ensembling is a statistical approach, which can also be related to the fields of neural networks (cs.NE) and multimedia (cs.MM). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV, followed by cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, and cs.MM.
